2.1. In this script, We load the data for the preprocess and normalization pipeline of Scanpy, show results without batch correction and convert data to the h5 file¶

Saving data by diopy¶

scDIOR links the preprocess and normalization pipeline of Scanpy and batch correction method of Seurat. When the normalized data is stored in the adata.raw, we recommed to save the adata.raw.X not adata.X by setting save_X = False. We can switch to Fig3b_R.ipynb for batch correction by using Seurat or use other batch correction method in Fig3b_Python.ipynb. Now we only implement batch correction by Seurat in R and load the batch correction result in the Python.
